these are the olympus one high heels
from a company called thesis couture
they're made out of a high-grade
ballistic level polymer which is
different than typical high heels which
are actually made out of a metal spike
and compressed cardboard so the shoes
are made out of three pieces and all of
them interlock so the toe box interlocks
up here on the bottom and then the heel
snaps off as well the goal of these
shoes is to provide arch support and to
take all of the pressure off of the toe
so what is actually a four inch high
heel feels like a three inch wedge these
hills are invented by a woman named
dolly Singh who used to be a recruiter
for companies like SpaceX and oculus so
she really knows her stuff
she basically recruited a bunch of
astronauts and MIT scientists and
Italian shoemakers and orthopedic
surgeons and have them designed this
custom shoe which is pretty much
one-of-a-kind so the shoes are also
actually really trendy they come in this
gladiator style which laces up your foot
and then this part ties around your
ankle I'm not really a high-heeled
person but I have to say they were the
most comfortable pair of high heels I've
ever worn so I've only tested them for
maybe 30 minutes to 45 minutes at a time
but I was amazed when I first put them
on by how much arch support there was
walking around and then you really
didn't feel like you were wearing high
heels this is a black pair but they also
come in a nude and gold color as well
the shoes cost 900 dollars so they are
pretty expensive but I think it's
justified if you go on thesis 2 towards
website you can sign up to be computer
for the pre-order but you should be
